metadata.name: Nishikigoi #62
metadata.description:
A calm exploration of generative koi ponds.
Infinitely procedurally animated.

Nishikigoi recreates the meditative experience of watching swimming koi. You may click to feed your koi fish, but only once every 30 minutes.

I hope you enjoy this little experience.

metadata.name: Circles #166
metadata.description:
“Circles” is a set of generative artwork make by sophisticatedly designed algorithm with surprising randomness. It explores different combinations of size, shape, color, arrangement, etc., trying to create different feeling about circles. 

I like circle because it’s a metaphor to the cycle of life, we start at one point and end at the same point. No matter the circle is big or small, thick or thin，colorful or dull, we experience it as a cycle.

Press the ’s’ key to save the image to your computer.

#This is the republish version of "Circle" as the old version contain a bug so I have to disable it. All holders have been refunded.

#For apology, the first 100 editions will be free for minting. And then there will be price increase every time when another 100 mints complete.

metadata.name: Elemental walks #40
metadata.description:
"Elemental walks" is an exploration of the interaction and perception of two different systems. The generated double grid pattern transforms into a crowd of random walkers that move in a random but constrained way, forming a dynamic pattern. You can change the colour, pause, reset, slow down or speed up your walkers.

"r" to reset position or release the walkers
"p" to toggle pause/play
"-" to slow down
"+" for faster movement
's' save png
'j' save jpg

Click the canvas and the colour composition changes.

metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #378
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash — they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Morixels Colab #1 CryptoMask #68
metadata.description:
We all have a mask and we hide our real selves behind it
What mask do you have?

The CryptoMask is unique random Generated 200 PFP NFTs.
The number of Traits in this collection is 8 (86 layers) and it has the ability to make unique 102,453,120 NFTs.

To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

This project is a collaboration project between Morteza Yousefi and Zahra Ghorbani and it is a Benefit for the owners of the most Morixels to Collaborate with Morixels Designer.

You can read more information on Morixels website 👇

Website: https://morixels.com/

Twitter: @Morixels

by: @morteza_yousefy & @mo0n_zi
Made in 2022

metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #111
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.
